{"id":"ev_f8d82106585749ee","runId":"run_218","type":"delegation","at":1782270029768,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_5e180afe25424869","atom":0,"task":"READ-ONLY RESEARCH ATOM (no product-code changes). Produce an evidence-backed research memo at docs/research/oz-flat-file-access.md that lets the founder choose the delivery mechanism for giving Oz read access to governed flat files (Playbooks, ADRs, persona/standards, workspace config) so Oz can answer governance/config questions in-session without an adhoc launch.\n\nThe ONLY file you may create/modify is docs/research/oz-flat-file-access.md. Do NOT touch any product code, tests, or config. This atom is research + a written memo, nothing else.\n\nGround every claim in the ACTUAL code with file:line citations. Investigate and document:\n\n1. SESSION-START DIGEST PATH (for Option A): Find where Oz's session/context prompt is assembled at session start and on Refresh. Identify the exact function(s) and file(s) that build the digest Oz receives. Quantify the current approximate context budget and where governed-file summaries would be injected. Cite file:line.\n\n2. BOUNDED TOOL SURFACE (for Option B): Find where Oz's callable tool surface is defined/registered (the bounded set of verbs Oz can invoke, e.g. the existing repair verb). Identify exactly where a new read-only `readGoverned(path)` tool would be registered, how tool calls are dispatched, and the existing pattern for scope-checking a path (any current allow-list / path-zone guard). Cite file:line. List the governed zones to allow: cocoder/decisions/, cocoder/priorities/, cocoder/personas/, cocoder/playbooks/, packages/personas/base/.\n\n3. OPTION A vs OPTION B COMPARISON: For each option, state concretely (a) what files change and roughly how much, (b) context-budget impact, (c) staleness behavior, (d) scope-check / security surface, (e) per-question cost (round-trips). Note whether a hybrid is viable.\n\n4. RECOMMENDATION: Pick one (or a hybrid) with a one-paragraph rationale tied to the cited evidence. Also identify the smallest provable build for the chosen mechanism, including how Option B's path-rejection (paths outside governed zones are refused) would be proven by a script.\n\nAcceptance criteria: the memo exists at docs/research/oz-flat-file-access.md; every structural claim about the digest path and tool surface has a real file:line citation that resolves to the current tree; the comparison covers all five dimensions for both options; a single clear recommendation is given. Must not break: no other file is modified."}}
